{
  "stem": "24259.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, again, my father was able to procure additional papers, because you couldn't move from one part of the country to another or from one country to another unless you had certain papers.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my father was able to get additional papers to enable us to go to Germany to the American zone, again, with the intent of emigrating to Israel.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the first time that I actually had seen a railroad, and I remember going on a railroad car.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And with other-- we met up with other refugees at that time, and we began traveling towards Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And, again, we were stopped in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They stopped the train with all the refugees on it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I believe it was the Czech government.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I also believe that, I think, the United States had something to do with that territory at that time, just from what I recall-- the conversations of my father and other people afterwards.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And apparently, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] whatever papers that we had were not-- they said they were not valid.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they made everybody get off the train, and they put us into a large-- I believe it was like a large hall or a gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they detained everybody there for several months while they were going through the legal hassle of allowing us to continue on our journey.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And fortunately, again, they straightened everything out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And again, I believe there was certain intervention with the American government at that time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they allowed us to continue on to the American part of German-- occupied Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is-- would be pretty close to, like, 1945.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'd say the middle of 1945, middle to the end of 1945.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
